last_episode_to_air.overview: Tripp's archeologist dad returns, but is taken captive

name: I'm in the Band
overview: Tripp Campbell is the new lead guitarist for Iron Weasel, a band that once ruled the world of 80s pop metal. Can he push the washed-up rockers out of his parents' guest room and back in the limelight?

episodes.name: Weasels In The House
episodes.overview: When Tripp Campbell wins a radio contest to meet his favorite band, Iron Weasel, he lands a spot as their new guitar player. Unfortunately, things take an unexpected turn when the band moves into Tripp's house.

episodes.name: I Wanna Punch Stuff
episodes.overview: Tripp gets dumped by Lana, the prettiest girl in his class so he's inspired to write a new song, "I Wanna Punch Stuff." Meanwhile, Tripp surprises his band mates with a visit from professional mixed martial arts fighter and former roadie, Ernesto the Besto, who unbeknownst to Tripp, has a bone to pick with Iron Weasel.

episodes.name: Slap Goes the Weasel
episodes.overview: A problem arises for Iron Weasel when their new move, the "Weasel Slap", is uploaded on video by Tripp. With this, Iron Weasel's reputation is compromised when a fan gets injured while performing the new move.

episodes.name: Annoying Arlene
episodes.overview: When Tripp finds out that Arelene, an annoying classmate, has a record producer for a father, he takes her out on a date in order to help out the band. However, a new Iron Weasel demo called "Annoying Arlene" accidentally falls into her hands. It's now up to the guys to get the CD back before anyone hears it.

episodes.name: Got No Class
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel and Tripp decide to film a music video. However, things get out of hand when they choose Tripp's school as the place to film it at. Being called an idiot for the last time, Ash decides to quit the band and becomes the new high school janitor.

episodes.name: Cat-astrophe
episodes.overview: Arlene invites Tripp and Iron Weasel to her house. However, they look at this as an opportunity to impress Arlene's record-producing father.

episodes.name: Flip of Doom
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel enters a televised rock off in order to "out rock" the reigning champions.

episodes.name: Birthdazed
episodes.overview: It's Tripp's birthday, but things get crazy when his mom and Iron Weasel both throw him a party on the same day.

episodes.name: Geezers Rock
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel decide to record a charity single for Tripp's grandmother's retirement home. But when the band purposely spends the money from the song on a sky-diving trip, They must perform community service to pay off their debt to the home.

episodes.name: Spiders, Snakes and Clowns
episodes.overview: Tripp gets Iron Weasel parts in a horror film  called "Spiders, Snakes, and Clowns". Unfortunately, the band is too scared to be a part of it, Burger being afraid of spiders, Derek being afraid of snakes, and Ash being afraid of clowns. Izzy tries to convince the director to let her be the part of the film.

episodes.name: Magic Tripp
episodes.overview: Tripp convinces Iron Weasel's former band manager to consider representing them again. However, the dinner becomes disastrous and it scares off their manager for the second time. As a last resort to win him over, Derek puts on a magic show.

episodes.name: What Happened?
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel is about to perform a major concert, but unfortunately for them they keep getting delayed. When their van breaks down, a pregnant woman, claiming to be a big fan, picks them up. However, things go from bad to worse when she goes into labor on their way to the concert.

episodes.name: Road Tripp
episodes.overview: Tripp is able to get Iron Weasel a concert tour, but unfortunately for them things get crazy.

episodes.name: Prank Week
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel goes too far with "Prank Week" and embarrasses Tripp in front of the whole school.

episodes.name: Money Bags
episodes.overview: Tripp gets back with Lana and encourages her to be less materialistic. But with Lana's new attitude means that she will not splurge money unnecessarily, that includes not hiring Iron Weasel for her birthday party and multiple monthly parties. Derek, Burger and Ash come up with a plan to try to change her attitude by throwing a party for Izzy to make Lana jealous.

episodes.name: Bleed Guitarist
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel's former guitarist "Bleed" comes back to try and get back in the band by taking Tripp's spot.

episodes.name: Weasels On Deck
episodes.overview: Cole and Dylan Sprouse from "The Suite Life On Deck" guest star on an episode of "I'm In The Band". Iron Weasal get to preform on the S.S. Tipton.

episodes.name: Izzy Gonna Sing
episodes.overview: Izzy's dreams come true when one of the band members looses their voice and she fills in.

episodes.name: Weasels vs. Robots
episodes.overview: Career day is coming up and Beth and Izzy are excited. But, Tripp isn't. Also, the magazine Cool Awesome wow gets a new Cover

episodes.name: Happy Fun Metal Rock Time
episodes.overview: Tripps books an interview for the band. But, a detention stands in the way. Meanwhile, Beth takes a self defence class

episodes.name: Last Weasel Standing
episodes.overview: The band creates a reality show but soon they find it is a lot of work.

episodes.name: I'm Out of the Band (1)
episodes.overview: Tripp leaves Iron Weasel in order to join their arch-rival rock band "Metal Wolf". So Derek, Ash and Burger try to lure him back into their band with help from Jerry Rice.

episodes.name: I'm Out of the Band (2)
episodes.overview: Tripp leaves Iron Weasel in order to join their arch-rival rock band "Metal Wolf". So Derek, Ash and Burger try to lure him back into their band with help from Jerry Rice.

episodes.name: Iron Weasel: The Video Game
episodes.overview: The band gets a chance to create their own Iron Weasel video game.

episodes.name: Extreme Weasel Makeover
episodes.overview: Tripp and the band try to convince Simon Craig to work with them as his clients.

episodes.name: Camp Weasel Rock
episodes.overview: The band holds a Rocky Fantasy Camp, a day camp where kids learn how to play a few songs and fulfill their dreams of being rock stars. When the guys realize that rock superstar Eddie Nova's kid is enrolled in their camp, they promise to turn his son, Junior, a quiet, classic cellist into a rock star, in exchange for being the opening act in Eddie's next tour.

episodes.name: Chucky's Revenge
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel is challenged with writing a new song for their record producer Simon Craig, while taking care of his son, Charles, who happens to be their number one fan. Charles claims to be an even tempered kid now, but the guys are suspicious of his behavior.

episodes.name: Burning Down the House
episodes.overview: The band accidentally burns down Tripp's house.

episodes.name: Who Dunnit?
episodes.overview: A Mystery Theater Dinner is under way and the band is not aware it's all for fun.

episodes.name: Yo Check My House
episodes.overview: The band decides to turn Beth's house into a rock star playground while she is out of town

episodes.name: Grand Theft Weasel
episodes.overview: Tripp tries to teach Derek, Burger and Ash a lesson about spending money frivolously

episodes.name: Don't Date The Principal's Daughter
episodes.overview: Trip's Principal does not want his daughter anywhere near him or the band. Trip can't keep away from her.

episodes.name: Weasels on a Plane
episodes.overview: The boys end up at the wrong airport on the wrong airplane, which crashes. They then decide to un-friend each other for a work-only relationship. It's up to Ash to save the day.

episodes.name: Lord of the Weasels
episodes.overview: Tripp, Ash and Burger sell the band van.  Derek gets caught up in some midevil role-playing trying to get the van back.

episodes.name: Weaselgate
episodes.overview: Izzy runs for school president

episodes.name: Prank Week 2
episodes.overview: The boys try to out-prank each other during the annual prank week.

episodes.name: Pain Games
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel challenges its rivals to a contest to determine who will play at the school dance

episodes.name: Iron Weasel Gets Schooled
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel makes a PSA to remind kids to stay in school - something none of the original members did.

episodes.name: Kicked Out for Band Behavior
episodes.overview: The band has to prove to Principal Jenkins that they are good role models when he sends social worker to Tripp's house

episodes.name: Iron Weasel vs Mini Weasel
episodes.overview: The band tries to prove that they are still rock stars with a plan even after being beaten by a band of look-alike little people.

episodes.name: Trippnotized
episodes.overview: Iron Weasel gets its big break and their rival band makes sure things go bad for them.

episodes.name: Raiders of the Lost Dad
episodes.overview: Tripp's archeologist dad returns, but is taken captive
